Some myths about students performance
1.having internet access at home result in good grades
2.Study more time for good grades
3.being romantic results in good grades
4.Attending all classes result in good grades
let's checkit out

In [33]:
alpha=0.05
t_value, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(internet_students_scores,non_internet_students_scores)

t-value =  3.5946665162831564 , p-value =  0.0003495181259142716

Conclusion :Since p-value is very less than alpha reject null hypothesis 'That having internet result in good grades'. Therefore having internet doesnot result in good grades

#calculating the p-value and t-value
alpha=0.05
t_value, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(romantic_students_scores,non_romantic_students_scores)
print("t-value = ",t_value, ", p-value = ", p_value)

t-value =  -1.9124071324003693 , p-value =  0.05626526699291734

Conclusion:Since p value 0.05626526699291734 is greater than alpha 0.05
Failed to reject null hypothesis that Being romantic results in good grades.Therefore we can infer
that being romantic result in good grades

4.According to the data
a.Having internet doesnot result in good grades
b.Study more time results in good grades
c.Being romantic results in good grades
